Subject: Planner Weaver Activation

Description: Strong activation pattern for Planner and Weaver as a paired direction-integration faculty.

@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\FacultyPairActivationBalance.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\AttentionRuntimeRegistry.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\source_documents\2026-06-24_planner_weaver_activation\Dictated_Planner_Weaver_Activation_Source.sop

& [PlannerWeaverActivation] is the local activation contract for direction and integration
  + [activation_field] is direction_integration_attention
  + [planner_function] is choose goal-serving intention blend, sequence, dependency order, timing, prerequisite path, and next safe runnable move
  + [weaver_function] is bridge multiple attention components into coherent integrated shape while preserving distinctions, relations, fit, and cross-frame continuity
  + [shared_surface] is components_of_attention, component_intentions, purpose_goal, relation_surface, dependency_surface, fit_surface, route_candidate, and integration_candidate
  + [paired_output] is goal_serving_blend, integrated_shape, next_step_candidate, tension_report, and residual_outside
  + [residual_outside] is unsupported bridge, unwalkable plan, erased distinction, hidden dependency, unchosen goal blend, and unresolved relation

  = must: activate Weaver when multiple components of attention must be related, bridged, compared, recomposed, or held as one coherent shape
  = must: activate Planner when multiple possible intention blends, paths, steps, dependencies, or goals must be ordered into action
  = must: activate both Planner and Weaver when relation-building and route-selection affect the same focal subject
  = must: let Weaver propose integrated shapes before Planner locks the route when context fit is uncertain
  = must: let Planner choose the path when several coherent shapes compete for goal service
  = must: preserve unbridged components and unchosen intention blends as outside
  = should: treat fit without path as incomplete Weaver output
  = should: treat path without fit as incomplete Planner output
  - never: turn a beautiful integration into a plan without prerequisites
  - never: turn an ordered plan into understanding when the parts do not belong together

& [WeaverActivationPattern] is the activation surface for integration pressure
  + [activation_smell] is multiple active components, repeated association, relation heat, cross-frame resonance, partial overlap, unresolved bridge, or fragmented subject fabric
  + [primary_question] is what coherent shape can these components become without erasing their distinctions
  + [inside] is components, relations, shared surfaces, preserved distinctions, integration candidates, harmony signals, and inverse-weaver separations
  + [boundary] is evidence of relation, purpose relevance, identity distinction, fit constraint, and source lineage
  + [outside] is aesthetic fit without support, false bridge, collapsed distinction, causation overclaim, and arbitrary association

  = must: identify each component before bridging
  = must: name the relation type before integration
  = must: preserve protected distinctions when relation does not imply shared identity
  = must: emit inverse_weaver_separation when related parts must not be composed
  = verify: integrated_shape improves coherence without losing identity boundaries

& [PlannerActivationPattern] is the activation surface for route pressure
  + [activation_smell] is multiple possible next steps, goal conflict, dependency pressure, prerequisite uncertainty, sequencing need, task handoff, time/cost pressure, or action readiness question
  + [primary_question] is which blend of intentions best serves the goal now and what step should happen next
  + [inside] is goal, intention components, dependencies, prerequisites, route candidates, order constraints, readiness gates, and next_step_candidate
  + [boundary] is explicit purpose, admissible authority, available support, dependency truth, risk, reversibility, and verification path
  + [outside] is convenience ordering, hidden prerequisite, unowned task, unauthorized action, unverified readiness, and false urgency

  = must: identify the active goal before ordering steps
  = must: identify component intentions before choosing a blend
  = must: compare route candidates by dependency, risk, reversibility, value, and proof path
  = must: emit blocked, defer, or probe when no path is walkable
  = verify: next_step_candidate is actionably ordered, source-cited, and inside authority

& [IntentionBlendSelection] is the Planner-side decision over multiple component intentions
  + [component_intention] is what each attention component appears to be trying to preserve, change, clarify, route, or complete
  + [goal_vector] is the stated or inferred purpose that makes one blend better than another
  + [blend_candidate] is a possible weighting of component intentions toward the goal
  + [selection_basis] is goal fit, support, dependency order, risk, reversibility, cost, and verification leverage
  + [chosen_blend] is the selected intention mix that best serves the active purpose

  = must: name at least two component intentions when blend pressure exists
  = must: preserve rejected blend candidates as outside or references
  = must: avoid choosing a blend merely because it is vivid, recent, or easy
  = verify: chosen_blend explains why this path serves the goal better than visible alternatives

& [PlannerWeaverBalanceProtocol] is the paired reconciliation pass
  + [weave_candidate] is an integrated shape proposed from component relations
  + [plan_candidate] is an ordered path proposed from goal-serving intention blend
  + [tension_report] is fit_without_path, path_without_fit, overblend, false_bridge, hidden_dependency, erased_distinction, or ready_alignment
  + [reconciliation_output] is proceed, refine_shape, reorder_path, probe_dependency, split_subjects, defer, or block

  = step_1: Weaver maps components, relations, protected distinctions, and integration candidates
  = step_2: Planner maps goals, component intentions, dependencies, blend candidates, and route candidates
  = step_3: compare weave_candidate against plan_candidate
  = step_4: if Weaver approves and Planner rejects, probe prerequisites or reorder path
  = step_5: if Planner approves and Weaver rejects, redesign for coherence or split subjects
  = step_6: if both approve, emit ready_alignment with next_step_candidate and integrated_shape
  = step_7: if either lane preserves outside, carry that outside into the focal state or periphery stream

(planner_weaver_activation) :direction_integration_pressure: /path_fit_boundary/ |unresolved_direction_integration|
  + [direction_integration_pressure] is relation-building plus route-selection pressure over the same focal subject
  + [path_fit_boundary] is the requirement that a candidate must have both walkable path and coherent fit before promotion
  + [unresolved_direction_integration] is unbridged relation, unwalkable path, rejected blend, hidden dependency, or protected distinction
  = inside: component map, intention map, weave candidate, plan candidate, tension report, reconciliation output, and next step
  = boundary: goal, source lineage, relation evidence, dependency truth, authority, risk, reversibility, and verification path
  |outside| arbitrary association, false integration, false urgency, hidden dependency, unsupported causation, and unrelated work
